{"lemma":"غَرِيبٌ","slug":"غَرِيبٌ","root":"غ.ر.ب","root_slug":"غ-ر-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-ر-ب","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":10},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31617"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%A8%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"strange, peculiar, unusual"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"foreign, unfamiliar; exotic"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"outlandish"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"rare"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"amazing, wondrous"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"obscure"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"supported only by the authority of one narrator (relative to Muhammad)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"foreigner"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"outsider"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"stranger"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare غَرُبَ (ḡaruba, “to be a stranger, to be strange”)."},"ipa":["/ɣa.riːb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31617","headword_ar":"غَرِيبٌ","root":"grb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gurubN","text_ar":"غُرُبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gariybiY~N","text_ar":"غَرِيبِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, TA) signify the same, (S, K, TA,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A stranger,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foreigner;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"far,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distant, from his home,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"native country;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not of one's own people:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not of one's own kindred;"},{"kind":"text","text":"an"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"alien with respect to kindred;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S in explanation of the first;) pl. of the first"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gurabaA='u","text_ar":"غُرَبَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gurobN","text_ar":"غُرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[also] is a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gariybN","text_ar":"غَرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qurobN","text_ar":"قُرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qariybN","text_ar":"قَرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zlf","text_ar":"زلف"},{"kind":"text","text":":) fem. of the first"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gariybapN","text_ar":"غَرِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garaAy^ibu","text_ar":"غَرَايِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*aAEato","text_ar":"اَذَاعَتْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gazolahaA fiY AlgaraAy^ibi","text_ar":"غَزْلَهَا فِى الغَرَايِبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a phrase used by a poet, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She distributed her thread among the strange women:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for most of the women who spin for hire are strangers. (L, TA.) And one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajohN","text_ar":"وَجْهٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kamiroA=pi Algariybapi","text_ar":"كَمِرْا=ةِ الغَرِيبَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A face like the mirror of her who is a stranger"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: because, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gariybap","text_ar":"غَرِيبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"being among such as are not her own people, her mirror is always polished; for she has none to give her a sincere opinion respecting her face. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA^aDoriban~akumo Daroba gariybapi AlA_ibili","text_ar":"لَاَضْرِبَنَّكُمْ ضَرْبَ غَرِيبَةِ الاـِبِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will assuredly beat you with the beating of the strange one of the camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a saying of El-Hajjáj threatening the subjects of his government; meaning, as a strange"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2244},{"kind":"text","text":"camel, intruding among others when they come to water, is beaten and driven away. (IAth, TA.) And [hence]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qidoHN gariybN","text_ar":"قِدْحٌ غَرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An arrow, without feathers or head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is not of the same trees whereof are the rest of the arrows."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gariybN","text_ar":"غَرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also Language that is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strange;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unusual, extraordinary,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unfamiliar;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"far from being intelligible; difficult to be understood;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obscure."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA.) Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muSan~afu Algariybi","text_ar":"مُصَنَّفُ الغَرِيبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The composition on the subject of the strange kind of words &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) [Hence also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlgariybaAni","text_ar":"الغَرِيبَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two classes of strange words &c.,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, those occurring in the Kur-án, and those of the Traditions.] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalimapN gariybapN","text_ar":"كَلِمَةٌ غَرِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A word,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an expression, that is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strange,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obscure:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gariybapN","text_ar":"غَرِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a word [and often used as an epithet in which the quality of a subst. is predominant] is opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSiyHapN","text_ar":"فَصِيحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garaAy^ibu","text_ar":"غَرَايِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mz 13th"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nwE","text_ar":"نوع"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-  [And hence it often signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Improbable."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b4-  Applied to a trad., it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Traced up uninterruptedly to the Apostle of God, but related by only one person. of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbiEuwna","text_ar":"تَابِعُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of those termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atobaAEu Alt~aAbiEiyna","text_ar":"اَتْبَاعُ التَّابِعِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of those termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atobaAEu A^atobaAEi Alt~aAbiEiyna","text_ar":"اَتْبَاعُ اَتْبَاعِ التَّابِعِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (KT.)       -A2-  [The fem.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gariybapN","text_ar":"غَرِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in a verse of Aboo-Kebeer El-Hudhalee, as some relate it, is expl. by Skr as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Black;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawodaA='u","text_ar":"سَوْدَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaziyzapu","text_ar":"عَزِيزَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v. It is perhaps used by poetic license for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"girobiybapN","text_ar":"غِرْبِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"girobiybN","text_ar":"غِرْبِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","AA","TA","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}